Package curam.util.client.domain.marshal

Contains functionality that allows the assembly of data that was split over several form fields by a renderer plug-in into a single value that can be submitted to the application server after parsing by the converter.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
DomainMarshal A domain marshal takes form data submitted by a user and converts it into a format that can be used to set a property of a BOPI.
 

Class Summary
AbstractDomainMarshal A base class for domain marshals.
AddressMarshal A domain marshal for addresses.
DateTimeMarshal A domain marshal for date time types.
SimpleXPathADCMarshal A marshal for string values that represent XML documents.
SimpleXPathMarshal A marshal for string values that represent XML documents.
SimpleXPathMarshal.DOMContextHelper A helper class that stores the DOM context node.
TextMarshal A simple marshal for domains with simple values.
 

Exception Summary
MarshalException Exception class for data marshalling problems.
 

Package curam.util.client.domain.marshal Description

Contains functionality that allows the assembly of data that was split over several form fields by a renderer plug-in into a single value that can be submitted to the application server after parsing by the converter.
